  "html": "<div class=\"facilis descensus Averno\"><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Etymology\">Etymology</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=facilis_descensus_Averno&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Etymology\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p>Literally &quot;The descent to Avernus is easy.&quot; From Virgil&apos;s <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeneid\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Aeneid\">Aeneid</a></i>, with reference to Avernus, a metonym for the underworld and to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Avernus\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Lake Avernus\">Lake Avernus</a> in Italy, a volcanic crater lake reputed to emit deadly vapors.\n</p><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pronunciation\">Pronunciation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=facilis_descensus_Averno&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Pronunciation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Classical Latin\">Classical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;fa.ki.lis de&#x2D0;s&#x2C8;ken.sus a&#x2C8;wer.no&#x2D0;/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;fa.k&#x26A;.l&#x2B2;&#x26A;s&#x320; d&#x32A;e&#x2D0;s&#x320;&#x2C8;k&#x1EBD;&#x2D0;.s&#x320;&#x28A;s&#x320; a&#x2C8;w&#x25B;r.no&#x2D0;]</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ecclesiastical Latin\">Ecclesiastical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;fa.t&#x361;&#x283;i.lis de&#x283;&#x2C8;&#x283;en.sus a&#x2C8;ver.no/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;fa&#x2D0;.t&#x361;&#x283;i.lis d&#x32A;&#x25B;&#x283;&#x2C8;&#x283;&#x25B;n.sus a&#x2C8;v&#x25B;r.n&#x254;]</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vulgar_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Vulgar Latin\">Vulgar</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;fa.ki.lis de&#x2D0;s&#x2C8;k&#x25B;n.sus a&#x2C8;&#x3B2;&#x25B;r.no&#x2D0;/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;fa.&#x261;e.les des&#x2C8;k&#x25B;n.sos a&#x2C8;&#x3B2;&#x25B;r.no]</span></li></ul><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Proverb\">Proverb</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=facilis_descensus_Averno&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Proverb\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/facilis#Latin\" title=\"facilis\">facilis</a></span> <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/descensus#Latin\" title=\"descensus\">d&#x113;scensus</a></span> <span class=\"Latn\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/Avernus#Latin\" title=\"Avernus\">Avern&#x14D;</a></span></strong>\n</p><ol><li>The <a href=\"/wiki/path\" title=\"path\">path</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/hell\" title=\"hell\">hell</a> is <a href=\"/wiki/easy\" title=\"easy\">easy</a>.\n<ul><li><b>29-19 <small class=\"ce-date\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#BCE\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\"><span title=\"Glossary and display preference\">B.C.E.</span></a></small></b> &#x2014; <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virgil\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Virgil\">Virgil</a>, <i><a href=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/la:Aeneis\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"s:la:Aeneis\">Aeneis</a></i>, Book VI, lines 124-127\n<dl><dd>Talibus orabat dictis, arasque tenebat,<br>cum sic orsa loqui vates: &quot;Sate sanguine divom,<br>Tros Anchisiade, <b>facilis descensus Averno</b>;<br>noctes atque dies patet atri ianua Ditis;&quot;\n<dl><dd>Then thus replied the prophetess divine:<br>&quot;O goddess-born of great Anchises&apos; line,<br>The gates of hell are open night and day;<br>Smooth the descent, and easy is the way:<br> (loose translation by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dryden\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:John Dryden\">John Dryden</a>, 1697)</dd></dl></dd></dl></li></ul></li></ol></div>"
